        <p class="t-body">For more information about cookies or to exercise your cookie preferences, please contact us using the information provided below.</p>

        <h2 class="t-headline-md">9. Do Not Track Signals</h2>
        <p class="t-body">Some web browsers offer a “Do Not Track” (DNT) feature that signals to websites that you do not want your online activities tracked. Because there is not yet a common industry standard for recognizing and responding to DNT signals, our website does not currently respond to DNT browser signals. As described in our Cookies Policy above, third parties may collect personal information about your online activities over time and across different websites when you use our website. You may manage tracking preferences through our cookie consent banner and your browser settings.</p>

